\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf1 SOLAR vs. LUNAR}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch \f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf1
\par\pard\plain \tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf1 The world has two moons. Given the important role that solar vs lunar understanding plays, there needs to be a solar calendar (the Helioptic one) and at least one major two-phase lunar calendar (the Barbo/Oober one).  Should work out the "actual" astronomy for this planet, including the seasons/weather patterns for "Saskantinon" and make sure the solar and lunar calendars align to it. }
\par\plain \f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf1 May be able to use some software to compute/estimate some of that.}
